# HOW TO USE

#install python 3.x.x from https://www.python.org/downloads/ and make sure to add it to PATH


# installing libraries
1)open cmd and trought cd navigate to folder.
2) type in cmd: pip install -r requirements.txt

# installing selenium.
# to make this work you need a webdriver. wich essentially is a method for selenium to communicate with the browser. to do so:
1) go to settings on your browser
2) about chrome and ctrl c the version

# if ur using chrome https://chromedriver.chromium.org/downloads
# if ur using firefox see https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/releases/

3) extract webdriver.exe from the folder and put it in the repository folder


# installing ffmpeg

1) Go to https://github.com/BtbN/FFmpeg-Builds/releases
2) install the version that suits you
3) open the folder and navigate to ffmpeg ecc.. -> bin -> ffmpeg.exe and drag it into the repo

# setting up the .py file.

1)now you'll need to enter your api hash and id to the script, to do so
  go to https://my.telegram.org/auth, and login with your number. create a new bot and get api 
  hash and id.

2) now open toimport.py with an editor (could be notepad too) 

3) search for (line 40) api id = and input your api id. same thing for api hash



# now you are ready to go! just type in cmd 
python main.py and the script will start by itself!(the first time you do this it will ask to access)
